text.section:
The Commission shall:
Establish policies directed toward improving the competitive position of the ports of Maryland within the international port industry;
Adopt regulations for the operation of the Administration in a competitive manner within the port industry;
Exercise those powers granted to the Commission and to the Maryland Port Administration by this title or by any other provision of law;
Unless otherwise directed by the Secretary, serve as the board of directors of any private operating company created under this title; and
In carrying out the provisions of this subtitle, seek information and advice from port labor and management groups.

section.section:
Subject to the provisions of paragraph (3) of this subsection, the Governor may not appoint to the Commission:
An officer or employee of the State;
A representative of any entity whose principal activities are ports-related;
A person employed by any entity whose principal activities are ports-related; or
A member of the General Assembly.
